      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 112: 🔴 Critical Issues - `resolved.exists()` alone can mark an incomplete or placeholder receive file as `TRANSFER_FINISHED` whenever daemon progress is stale at 0. That would hide the download button for incoming files that still need to be downloaded. Gate this filesystem fallback to sent/local messages, or at least verify the local file size matches `totalSize` when `totalSize \u003e 0`.\n\n```suggestion\n            QFileInfo resolved(body);\n            if (resolved.exists() \u0026\u0026 totalSize \u003e\u003d 0 \u0026\u0026 resolved.size() \u003d\u003d totalSize) {\n                transferStatus \u003d TransferStatus::TRANSFER_FINISHED;\n            } else {\n                transferStatus \u003d TransferStatus::TRANSFER_AWAITING_HOST;\n            }\n```",
